Question 21.Question: A crucible of 5gm weighed 10gm after filling with fresh soil. It is then heated in an oven at 1000C for 1hour. After cooling in desiccators the weight was 8gm. The percentage of water in the soil is
Question 21.Explanation:
The weight of the crucible = 5gm

Weight of crucible + soil = 10gm

Weight of soil = (10 – 5)gm = 5gm

Dehydration caused by heating leads to a reduction in the mass of the crucible.

The new weight of soil + crucible = 8gm

Weight of dry (dehydrated) soil = 8gm - 5gm = 3gm

So, we have 2gm of water, × 100% = 40%

= 0.4
